EJIKEME OMENAZU Beulah World Initiatives (BWI) in furtherance of its objective of meeting the needs of widows, the elderly and vulnerable people reached out to inhabitants of Idimu, in the outskirt of Lagos last Saturday. BWI, an Evangelical Outreach, a non-profit and non-government organisation, gave out items such as clothes, shoes, handbags, school bags, toys, among others, to many elders, women and children The outfit also gave talks on nutrition, free HIV tests and provided them with free medical treatment and reading glasses. According to the Coordinator of BWI, Ms Chichi Ononiwu, the initiative’s main objective is to make other people happy, adding, “Nothing is really as fulfilling as making others happy.” According to her, “What one takes for granted is most often a miracle to another.”